post_text: Juneteenth 2020 marks 155 years since news of the Emancipation Proclamation reached enslaved people in Texas, enforcing it by decree and finally freeing the last enslaved Americans two and a half years after it was signed. Today we celebrate the promise of freedom, and the ongoing fight for justice and equality.

Hoboken
January 3 at 6:11 PM ¬∑

The three free public charter schools in Hoboken - Elysian Charter School, Hoboken Dual Language Charter School (HOLA) and Hoboken Charter School - are accepting applications for the 2020-2021 school year. Applications must be submitted to each respective school no later than 5:00 pm sharp on January 9, 2020 to be entered into each school's randomized lottery. Please be reminded that these schools are mission-based, free public schools. More information on each school as well as their applications can be found on their websites.

In addition, the Hoboken School District, the largest provider of free public education in the City welcomes and enrolls all students into its comprehensive academic, theater, athletics, instrumental music, art, STEM, and co-curricular extended day programs on an ongoing basis. More information can be found on the Hoboken Public School District website.
